{"id": "1442812415551995964", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "content": "It's 1:30am for me so I need to sleep but tomorrow I'll send some DMs your way.\n\nThe main thing is, I want the Card Types at the bottom of each card expanded upon; I've been writing effects (just about finished with WoDs) with the assumption that my request is reasonable and can be implemented:\n\nAdd \"Strike Command\", \"Defense Command\" and possibly \"Skill Command\" to the type line, like how \"Derived Command\" is displayed, and allow for effects like Enlightens or Relics (like Sudden Fallacy) to change this type line instead of \"is considered \"Strike\"\"", "timestamp": "2025-11-25T09:41:26.026000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["1376763322568937562"], "reply_to": "1442810903065137303"}
{"id": "1442812758705049661", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "content": "When I say I've been wording things with that in mind I can provide this to chew on as an example of referencing both the name and the type separately\n# Will Unyielding\n- Desc:\n> The wielder's Base DMG and Shield gained from their effects both increase by `X%`.\n> When investigation begins, add one of the wielder's \"Strike\" and one of their \"Defense\" to the deck.\n> Whenever you play one of their Strike Commands, the Shield gained from their next Defense Command increases by 15%;\n> Whenever you play one of their Defense Commands, the Crit. Rate & Crit. DMG of their next Strike Command increase by +15%.\n> These effects can stack up to 3 times, and persist between battles.", "timestamp": "2025-11-25T09:42:47.840000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-11-25T09:43:33.993000+00:00"}
